                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4478.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Beaupré states that very early yesterday morning a revolution took place in
                    the city of San Juan, capital of the province of the same name. The
                    revolutionists expelled the provincial government and established provisional
                    government; took the government house, police station, and prison. Mr. Beaupré
                    also states that the Federal Government intervened and, pending the decision of
                    the arbiter, has taken control without opposition from the revolutionists.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
